Description: nderground is a social network that allows its users to share with the people in their life and maintains privacy.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: nderground is for anyone who wants to share their life with their friends and family, without worrying about public exposure. nderground is for families who want to post pictures of their children without exposing them to the larger internet. nderground is for doctors, lawyers, law enforcement and people who hold security clearances. In short, nderground is for anyone who is conderned about privacy. On other social networks you have to carefully curate your public presence. On nderground you can be yourself. Social networks like Facebook, Google+ and LinkedIn are designed for public exposure. Corporations and other groups join these social networks for publicity and to communicate with their customers. The public nature of social networks often results in unintended exposure. Some people are reminded that the material that they post is visible to over a billion people when it goes viral. Photographs posted on a social network of drinking or using illegal drugs have resulted in job offers being withdrawn. nderground is not like other social networks. No corporation will never include the link "find us on nderground" on their corporate web page. Other social networks are designed for public display and publicity. nderground is constructed from "the ground up" with privacy in mind. nderground users can go by their "handle" - there is no "true name" requirement on nderground. An nderground member is known only to their connections. On nderground these connections are called a Karass (a reference inspired by Kurt Vonnegut's book Cat's Cradle). Content that is posted on nderground can only be seen by a member's Karass (an exception exists for the nderground administrators).

Full Description: The law firm of Rey Padron, PLLC is a personal injury law firm in Miami Lakes serving clients who have been injured due to negligence. Our attorneys can assist you if you've been injured in; a car accident, slip, and fall, while working, while shopping, and many other areas of the law. Our lawyers are known for having a personalized approach that ensures each case gets our full attention. Our goal is to make sure that you are treated fairly and are fully compensated for your time and injuries. We will work with you to explain the entire process. Communication is important to us, which is why we make it a priority to reply promptly to our clients when they have questions about their claims. Car accidents can be devastating for everyone involved. It's no wonder that so many people suffer from injuries after car accidents, some of them serious or even fatal. The aftermath of a car accident is usually chaos as people try to figure out how they will pay their medical bills, replace damaged property, and take care of other issues created by the accident. In addition, there may be criminal charges if someone was driving under the influence or if another driver was texting while driving causing an accident with injuries or fatalities. For those who have suffered an injury because of these types of incidents, it is important to understand what legal rights you have as well as what compensation may be available through insurance claims and lawsuits against negligent parties responsible for the crash. Working with the right attorneys after an accident is crucial if obtaining compensation is important for you.

Description: Still pushing ahead to a late-summer emergence from bankruptcy, PhyCor is playing the rename game.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Still pushing ahead to a late-summer emergence from bankruptcy, PhyCor is playing the rename game. Earlier this year the company announced it would change tack and switch its name to Aveta Health Inc. The changes are spilling into its other business areas as CEO Tarpley Jones and Phycor move toward a fresh start. Jones, formerly the company's chief financial officer replaced Thompson S. Dent as president and CEO of the Nashville physician practice management company earlier this year. Within the past few months, the company has formed Pivot Health as a wholly owned subsidiary to take the place of PhySis, its hospital clinic management operation. "It will be the entity that will inherit Phycor's hospital-based clinic management business. We've had that business for several years," says Jones. "We wanted to give it another name and we're renaming a number of companies and subsidiaries." He says Pivot is outside of the bankruptcy proceedings, as was its predecessor. The company provides executive management for large, multi-specialty clinics within hospitals on a contract basis, Jones says. "It was started two or three years ago and it's very profitable," he says. The company's revenues are in the $4 million range, Jones says. As for Phycor-turned-Aveta, Jones says the company should be ready to emerge from bankruptcy before the end of the summer.
